how do you make crispy chicken how can you make somthing like kfcs crispy chicken there's no kfc in my country d ingredients pound chicken cut into pieces cup buttermilk cups all purpose flour for coating teaspoon paprika salt and pepper to taste quarts vegetable oil for frying directions take your cut up chicken pieces and skin them if you prefer put the flour in a large plastic bag let the amount of chicken you are cooking dictate the amount of flour you use season the flour with paprika salt and pepper to taste paprika helps to brown the chicken dip chicken pieces in buttermilk then a few at a time put them in the bag with the flour seal the bag and shake to coat well place the coated chicken on a cookie sheet or tray and cover with a clean dish towel or waxed paper let sit until the flour is of a paste like consistency this is crucial fill a large skillet cast iron is best about to full with vegetable oil heat until very hot put in as many chicken pieces as the skillet can hold brown the chicken in hot oil on both sides when browned reduce heat and cover skillet let cook for minutes the chicken will be cooked through but not crispy remove cover raise heat again and continue to fry until crispy drain the fried chicken on paper towels depending on how much chicken you have you may have to fry in a few shifts keep the finished chicken in a slightly warm oven while preparing the rest Tofu Bread Japanese cuisine Cookware and bakeware Jewish cuisine French fries Cajun cuisine Cantonese cuisine Cuisine of the Philippines Soul food Cuisine of Malaysia Pizza Barbecue Cuisine of the Southern United States Fried chicken Cuisine of Denmark Casting Hamburger Haggis Chili con carne D__ner kebab Cuisine of Brazil Korean cuisine In-N-Out Burger McDonald's German cuisine Ramen Bacon Dosa Plastic Idli Coffee Breakfast Dairy Wok Kentucky Fried Chicken Fish and chips Puff pastry Curry Mayonnaise Dim sum Cuisine of Singapore Russian cuisine Manicure Cookie Dumpling Peruvian cuisine 